    "caption": "We arrived where the jungle still breathes\nAmong gentle cows and baboons with ancient eyes.\nThe realization settled quietly deep:\nThis sacred land was never ours alone.\n\nBeneath the cliff, water lilies stretched placidly, infinitely.\nMonkeys mirrored our ascent, sharing the trail,\nToward massive claws gripping the earth in perpetual guard.\n\nThrough the stone sentinel’s grip, the summit.\nThe heavy sky turned to a misty, tactile grace,\nA soft rain falling as the world dissolved,\n\nAnd the earth reflected back into our soul.",
